args:
This shop is just one of many secret lairs
I have across the continent, and I swear
no one will ever find you here. Now then,
how about a mug of hot cocoa?
So now you're stealing people? Well,\nI suppose you did learn from the best.
Be it works of art or children, if something\nneeds rescuing, the Blue Rose is there
Heh, that's exactly what the last Blue Rose\nused to say... Anyway, who's the kid?
Her name is Aisha. Until recently, she\nlived with her mother in a small village.
But that man Radelle had some of his\nthugs come in and take me.
Kidnapping, is it? Interesting. So why did\nRadelle want you in particular?
Have a look at this: It's an ancient\nmanuscript I found in Radelle's mansion\nwhile I was rescuing Aisha.
It says there's an ancient treasure hidden\nin the Crouce Ruins—one you need a\ncertain key to get.

This key is said to have been passed
down through the generations of a certain
family—and I assume you're smart enough
to put two and two together here, non?
The key comes from the family of my\ndeceased father, but I don't really know\nanything about it myself.
So Radelle is after that treasure, eh?\nWell? What are you going to do?
Do you even need to ask? All treasure\nmust be returned to its rightful place!
Hmph. All right, let me get you a map.\nBut you'll have to figure out the best route\nfor yourself, apprentice.
Wait, you're taking me back to my village?\nOh no! I can't ask you to do that!
Returning stolen treasure is ever the duty\nof the Blue Rose, my dear.
Hmm? Weird, someone's at the door.\nStore is closed today.
Sorry to butt in, but we're makin' the\nrounds in this quarter to ask some\nquestions.

The daughter of the head of the Radelle
Corporation's been kidnapped. Name's
Aisha. The perpetrators are hiding nearby.
Happen to know anything?
His DAUGHTER?! Hardly! Plus, that guy\nis the one who kidnapped ME!
Such a bold-faced lie makes it easier for\nthem to look for you. Still, I'm surprised\nthey managed to track us so quickly.
Radelle is rotten to his core, but he's a\ngood businessman—I'm sure he's got his\nown information network to leverage.
I'll deal with the jokers at the door.\nYou take the girl out the back.
Merci, I owe you. Let's go, little one.
Hold on, I'm coming. You want some\ncocoa while you're waiting there?
Buddy, I would LOVE me some cocoa.
Nope. Even recruited some volunteers\nto help, but nothing so far.
Radelle's henchmen are everywhere.\nWe'll never make it out of town!
If there's no escape route, we shall just\nhave to make one. Hold on tight, Aisha!
First we shoot up into the air, and next\nthing I know, here we are on the roof...
I used a wire to fling us up here.\nNow we can spirit ourselves from town.
Uh, did you hear something on the roof?
Likely just a rat. But back to the person\nyou're looking for, I can't say I've seen \nanyone fitting her description.
Well, we appreciate your help anyway.\n...So, Ranzal? Where to next?
I vote we follow them footsteps what\nwe just heard from the roof.
We did it! We made it out of town!\nThat means we're safe, right?
Non. Our pursuers seem the stubborn sort,\nand I wouldn't be surprised if they're\nwaiting for us in your village.

Non again. Not to put too fine a point on
it, but Radelle has little interest in YOU—
he cares only about your key and the
treasure it can lead him to.
But if someone were to steal that treasure,\nyou would hold no further interest for him.
The Crouce Ruins aren't far. Why don't\nwe just go there and get the treasure?
I told you, I don't know anything about\nthis key everyone seems to want!
Perhaps you do and just don't know it.
Besides, this is my problem now. If I can't\nput you back in your rightful place, it will\ndamage the good name of the Blue Rose.
It's settled, then. To the ruins!
Yeah, we're gonna need ya ladies\nto hold on for just a tick.
Bonjour, Prince! Fancy meeting you\nand your bonny companions here.
The head of the Radelle Corporation asked\nfor help finding his kidnapped daughter.
And the kid right there is pretty much\na dead ringer for her description.
If I told you we're having a tea party,\nwould you believe me?
Yeah, I ain't interested in fallin' for\none'a yer clever tricks again, thanks.
Plus, we KNOW yer a thief,\nso we can't just be lettin' ya go.
I'm afraid we lack the time for proper\nexplanations at the moment, child.
No! It's the Radelle company goons!
We're taking you in, Lapis. It's time for\nyou to answer for all of your crimes.
If there truly is an explanation for what\nyou're doing here, we're willing to listen.\nPerhaps you'll even earn some leniency.
Ah, the classic tough-but-fair approach.\nBut you needn't bother, for I fear I've no\nintention of being caught.

Ya talk a big game for someone who's
outnumbered. Oh, and if yer plannin' to
use one'a them smokescreens again,
we're ready for it this time.
Oh, I've something else in mind for you,\nmy large friend. ...Voilà!
Aw, sweet cripes! A flash bomb!
Damn it! She got away AGAIN! This lady's\nreally startin' to grate my cheese...
I think we're safe for now...
This will prove more difficult than I\nimagined if the Halidom is involved.
But I am not giving up, for the phantom\nthief laughs in the face of even the\ngravest of dangers!
Just like the one who stole me away\nall those many years ago...
